Two businessman from Mutulani trading centre, Mukaa area, were butchered on Saturday night by gangsters armed with crude weapons.Police fired in the air and used teargas teargas to disperse the crowd of residents protesting against increased crime.The victims were Wambua Ndeti, 40, who ran a hotel, and Francis Munyao, 30, who ran a wedding business.Makueni police commander Joseph Napeiyan told the Star on the phone yesterday the bodies were found by a milk supplier. He said nothing was stolen from the victims, whose throats were slit. There were deep panga cuts in the men&rsquo;s legs and thighs.Police had a hard time removing the bodies from the same scene after residents blocked the road, protesting against the rising crime and violence.